Is the best way to close the parent window when a child window needs to be closed.

A:

For security reasons, it's not possible to access another windows context from within another windows context.
What you could do is set a variable in the parent window to be able to access the child window from the parent window:
// Parent.js
var childWindow = null;

function openChildWindow() {
   childWindow = window.open("child.html");
   // Do something with the child window
}

function closeChildWindow() {
   if (childWindow) {
      childWindow.close();
      childWindow = null;
   }
}

And then call those functions from the child window:
// Child.html
<button onclick="closeChildWindow()">Close child window</button>

Please note that this is just some suggestions on how you could implement this. There are other ways to do this as well.
